      • getChanged

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getChanged()
                                                    throws TMDbResponseException
        Gets a list of movie ids that have been edited. By default we show the last 24 hours and only 100 items per page. The maximum number of days that can be returned in a single request is 14. You can then use the getChanged(int) static method to get the actual data that has been changed. Please note that the change log system to support this was changed on October 5, 2012 and will only show movies that have been edited since. Returns the results of the first page.

      • getAllChanged

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getAllChanged(java.util.Date start,
                                              java.util.Date end)
                                                       throws TMDbResponseException
        Gets the entire list of movie ids that have been edited. By default we show the last 24 hours and only 100 items per page. The maximum number of days that can be returned in a single request is 14. You can then use the getChanged(int) static method to get the actual data that has been changed. Please note that the change log system to support this was changed on October 5, 2012 and will only show movies that have been edited since. Returns the results of the first page.
        Parameters:
        start - The date where the search starts
        end - The date where the search ends
        Returns:
        List of movie ids that have been edited.
        Throws:
        TMDbResponseException - Throws whether the server response is not a success.
